cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

The paper deals with pain assessment through facial images, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of a semi-supervised learning procedure, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The focus on special categories of patients such as neonates and patients with dementia suggests a potential fit with cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The use of facial images for pain assessment also involves the analysis of emotions, which could be related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
